  "prompt": "How do you know who viewed you video on Instagram?",
  "response": "On Instagram, you can see who viewed your videos if they are posted on Instagram Stories or IGTV. Here's how to check views for each:\n\n1. **Instagram Stories:**\n   - Open your Instagram app.\n   - Go to your Story by tapping on your profile picture at the top left.\n   - Swipe up on the screen while viewing your Story.\n   - You'll see a list of accounts that viewed each individual Story slide.\n\n2. **IGTV Videos:**\n   - Go to your profile and tap on the IGTV tab (the TV icon).\n   - Select the video you want to check.\n   - Below the video, you will see the view count, and if you tap on it, it will show you a list of people who have viewed the video.\n\nFor regular posts (videos shared on your feed), you can see the total number of views but cannot see the specific users who watched the video. The view count can be found under the video itself.\n\nKeep in mind that privacy settings may affect whether you can see views or not.",
